THIRD-PARTY NOTICES
====================

This project is a research extension built on top of existing open-source
software. The following third-party components are included:


1. VICE Chess Engine (Video Instructional Chess Engine)
------------------------------------------------------
   Author:    Richard Allbert (Bluefever Software)
   Website:   http://www.bluefever.net
   Tutorial:  https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLZ1QII7yudbc-Ky058TEaOstZHVbT-2hg
   Year:      2013-2014 (Vice 1.0 and 1.1)
   License:   Open-use (author's statement: "You are welcome to use the code
              as you like to help with your projects!")

   The following Source/ files are original VICE code (some with minor
   modifications for LLM integration, noted inline):
     attack.c, bitboards.c, board.c, data.c, defs.h, evaluate.c,
     hashkeys.c, init.c, io.c, makemove.c, misc.c, movegen.c, perft.c,
     polybook.c, polykeys.c, polykeys.h, pvtable.c, search.c, uci.c,
     validate.c, vice.c, xboard.c

   Files modified from the original VICE source:
     - search.c   : Added LLM fallback integration, fixed operator
                     precedence bug, removed dead-code guard
     - vice.c     : Added curl_global_init/cleanup in main()
     - uci.c      : Fixed INPUTBUFFER macro precedence
     - defs.h     : Changed system header includes to angle brackets,
                     renamed engine identification string


